            "text": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: `--set-ix-account` CLI option for simulate\n\n## Context\nUsers need to swap account pubkeys within specific instructions of a transaction before simulation. This enables testing \"what if instruction X used account Y instead?\" scenarios without re-signing transactions.\n\n## CLI Design\n```\nsonar simulate \u003cTX\u003e --set-ix-account 0.2=So11111111111111111111111111111112\n```\n- Format: `\u003cIX_INDEX\u003e.\u003cACCOUNT_POSITION\u003e=\u003cNEW_PUBKEY\u003e`\n- `IX_INDEX`: 0-based instruction index\n- `ACCOUNT_POSITION`: 0-based position in the instruction's account list (not the program_id)\n- `NEW_PUBKEY`: the replacement pubkey\n- Flag can be repeated: `-A 0.2=Key1 -A 1.0=Key2`\n- Short flag: `-A`\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Step 1: Add type `InstructionAccountSwap` in `crates/sonar-sim/src/types/accounts.rs`\n```rust\npub struct InstructionAccountSwap {\n    pub instruction_index: usize,\n    pub account_position: usize,\n    pub new_pubkey: Pubkey,\n}\n```\n\n### Step 2: Add `apply_ix_account_swaps()` in `crates/sonar-sim/src/transaction.rs`\nFunction that mutates a `ParsedTransaction` in-place:\n1. Validate `instruction_index` \u003c number of instructions\n2. Validate `account_position` \u003c instruction's accounts length\n3. Check if `new_pubkey` already exists in `message.static_account_keys()`\n4. If not, append it to the message's `account_keys` vec (works for both Legacy and V0 messages)\n5. Update `instructions[ix_index].accounts[account_position]` to the new pubkey's index (as `u8`)\n6. Update `account_plan.static_accounts` to match\n\nRe-export from `crates/sonar-sim/src/lib.rs`.\n\n### Step 3: Add CLI arg + parser in `src/cli/simulate.rs`\n- Add `ix_account_swaps: Vec\u003cString\u003e` field to `SimulateArgs` with `--set-ix-account` / `-A` flag under `HELP_HEADING_STATE_PREPARATION`\n- Add `parse_ix_account_swap()` function: splits on `=`, then splits left side on `.`, parses ix index, account position, and pubkey\n- Add unit tests for the parser\n\n### Step 4: Wire up in handler `src/handlers/simulate.rs`\n- Parse the CLI strings into `Vec\u003cInstructionAccountSwap\u003e` (alongside existing replacements/fundings parsing)\n- Call `apply_ix_account_swaps(\u0026mut parsed_tx, \u0026swaps)?` **before** `prepare_accounts_and_idls()` so the new pubkeys are included in account loading\n- Do the same in `handle_bundle()`\n\n## Key files to modify\n- `crates/sonar-sim/src/types/accounts.rs` — new type\n- `crates/sonar-sim/src/transaction.rs` — mutation logic\n- `crates/sonar-sim/src/lib.rs` — re-export\n- `src/cli/simulate.rs` — CLI arg + parser\n- `src/handlers/simulate.rs` — wiring\n\n## Verification\n1. `cargo build` — compiles\n2. `cargo test` — existing + new unit tests pass\n3. Manual test: take a known transaction and use `--set-ix-account` to swap an account, verify the simulation runs with the swapped account\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/oker/.claude/projects/-Users-oker-Source-sonar/d0ab56b6-ae31-4c51-abc6-409553ab222a.jsonl",
